~ Website Goals & Objectives

Provide updated Chelsea news for South African fans.

Showcase team information and match-related content.

Improve community interaction using enquiry and contact forms.

Build an engaging, responsive, visually appealing website.

Add dynamic JavaScript-powered interaction for a modern experience.

Implement strong SEO best practices for improved discoverability.

~ Key Features & Functionality
Part 1

Sitemap and website structure planned.

Five fully functional HTML pages created.

Content research completed for all pages.

Basic navigation and page linking.

Part 2

Full CSS styling with colour scheme and typography.

Brand theme inspired by Chelsea FC blue (#034694).

Responsive layout with Flexbox/Grid.

Hover effects, improved spacing, and legibility.

Styled header, footer, gallery, cards, and sections.

Part 3 (Full JavaScript & SEO Enhancements)

~JavaScript Interactivity Added

Accordion sections for FAQ or news items.

Search bar to filter players or news.

Lightbox gallery pop-up for images.

Animation effects using CSS + JS triggers.

Dynamic content updating (e.g., loading players list).

Scroll-to-top button.

Mobile navigation toggle.

~ Form Validation Added

Contact form validation using JavaScript.

Enquiry form validation for correct format:

Name

Email

Message

Phone number

Drop-down enquiry reason

Error messages and success confirmation.

Required fields defined using HTML5 attributes.

✔ SEO Improvements Implemented

Meta descriptions for all pages.

Structured H1, H2 hierarchy.

Alt text added to all images.

Clean, semantic HTML tags used (header, nav, main, footer).

Mobile responsive viewport meta tag.

Internal linking between pages.

Descriptive filenames for images.

Added robots.txt and sitemap.xml.

~ Additional Enhancements

Interactive map (Leaflet or Google Maps).

Smooth scrolling behaviour.

Page speed improvements (compressed images).

